{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Xca44LGmY5cfQ6zcU7yuL5","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `repository-s3` module is available as a built-in module (not a plugin). This means no installation needed. Now I need to:\n\n1. Create the `es-secure-settings` secret with the MinIO credentials\n2. Add the credentials to the Elasticsearch keystore on each node\n3. Configure the S3 client endpoint in elasticsearch.yml (but without putting credentials there)\n4. Register the snapshot repository \"minio-repo\"\n5. Create a snapshot\n\nFor the S3 client configuration (endpoint, protocol, path-style access), these go in `elasticsearch.yml`. Only the credentials (access key and secret key) go in the keystore.\nThe endpoint and protocol settings aren't credentials, so they're safe for elasticsearch.yml. I'll create the `es-secure-settings` secret with the MinIO access and secret keys using `minio` as the client identifier, then add those credentials to the keystore on each Elasticsearch node. https) settings, and `path_style_access` can go directly in elasticsearch.yml since they're not secrets. I'm realizing that while the `reload_secure_settings` API can refresh keystore credentials in newer Elasticsearch versions, the elasticsearch.yml configuration changes will require a restart anyway, so I need to plan for that downtime. The endpoint setting must live in elasticsearch.yml as part of the client configuration—it can't be specified at the repository level. So I'll need to update the ConfigMap with the S3 client settings, add the credentials to the keystore, and then restart the pods to apply those changes before registering the repository and creating the snapshot.\n\nCreating the Kubernetes Secret...\n\nI need to decide whether to use exec commands to add keystore entries on each pod or use an init container approach. The exec method is simpler but the changes won't persist after a restart, so I'll need to update the StatefulSet with an init container that reads the credentials from the Secret and populates the keystore before Elasticsearch starts. Then I can update the ConfigMap with the S3 client settings and do a rolling restart.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":468,"cache_read_input_tokens":34768,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":468},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ae89d6f6-ac7a-49ae-94ca-dcf73a9f115a","uuid":"f8bb3088-ef4a-446f-8d20-c4f37bb025ed","request_id":"req_011CcexApmt5tEdw1ByaYxwa"}
