{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_019TvkYwSoVi8fJWTkK9MM8T","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, I see the issue. The `keystore-setup` init container mounts `config-writable` (an emptyDir) at `/usr/share/elasticsearch/config`. But the main container does NOT mount `config-writable` anywhere. The main container only has the standard mounts.\n\nThis means:\n- The init container writes the keystore to the emptyDir\n- The main container uses its own overlay FS for `/usr/share/elasticsearch/config/` (which has the original keystore)\n- The init container's keystore changes are NOT seen by the main container\n\nI need to also add the `config-writable` emptyDir to the main container's volumeMounts at `/usr/share/elasticsearch/config/`.\nBut mounting the emptyDir there would hide the image's config files like jvm.options and log4j2.properties. However, since ES_JAVA_OPTS is already set to override JVM memory settings, losing jvm.options is fine. The real concern is log4j2.properties—without it, logging might not work as expected.\n\nActually, I realize the emptyDir approach is still the cleanest solution. I'll mount it at `/usr/share/elasticsearch/config/` in both the init container and main container, and rely on ES's built-in logging defaults if log4j2.properties isn't present. Now I need to update the StatefulSet to add this volumeMount to the main container.\n\nUpdating the StatefulSet patch...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1312,"cache_read_input_tokens":52100,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1312},"output_tokens":27,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ae89d6f6-ac7a-49ae-94ca-dcf73a9f115a","uuid":"374a49b5-a98a-43f3-a2f0-fb874f65846d","requ