{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_0152kv97VLo1kJHThfCTipXo","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The init container has TWO volumeMounts for `config-writable`:\n1. `/esconfig-writable` → config-writable\n2. `/usr/share/elasticsearch/config` → config-writable\n\nThis happened because my patch MERGED with the existing volumeMounts instead of replacing them. The first patch had `/usr/share/elasticsearch/config` and the second patch added `/esconfig-writable`, so both are now present.\n\nBecause the emptyDir `config-writable` is mounted at `/usr/share/elasticsearch/config/` in the init container, the image files are hidden there. That's why `log4j2.properties` is not found.\nI need to replace the init container's volumeMounts entirely to only have the `/esconfig-writable` mount. The strategic merge patch merges arrays by default, but since the init container uses `name` as the key, specifying the full init container definition should replace it completely.\n\nHowever, I realize the issue: when I provided patches with different mountPaths, they both got merged into the array instead of replacing it. I need to use a JSON patch with an explicit replace directive to set the volumeMounts array directly, rather than relying on the strategic merge behavior.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":609,"cache_read_input_tokens":62266,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":609},"output_tokens":35,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ae89d6f6-ac7a-49ae-94ca-dcf73a9f115a","uuid":"b5dd78a2-7280-4768-88ce-b1d36046e243","request_id":"req_011CcexcxiqWvHahynFP6Rfs"}
