{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_018cZ9JRCvBer76avP9LbJi7","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is complete and verified. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**What was configured:**\n\n1. **MinIO Service** — The `minio` service was missing (the `minio-init` job had failed because of this). Created a ClusterIP service exposing port 9000 at `minio.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local`.\n\n2. **MinIO `es-backups` bucket** — Created via `mc` inside the MinIO pod.\n\n3. **`es-secure-settings` Secret** — Created with `s3.client.minio.access_key` and `s3.client.minio.secret_key` (credentials never placed in elasticsearch.yml or env vars).\n\n4. **`es-config` ConfigMap updated** — Added three static S3 client settings (safe to put in YAML — these are not credentials):\n   - `s3.client.minio.endpoint: minio.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local:9000`\n   - `s3.client.minio.protocol: http`\n   - `s3.client.minio.path_style_access: true`\n\n5. **StatefulSet patched** — Added a `keystore-setup` init container that runs on every pod start to:\n   - Copy `log4j2.properties`, `jvm.options`, and `jvm.options.d/` from the image into a shared emptyDir\n   - Create a fresh keystore in the emptyDir and populate it with the S3 credentials from the `es-secure-settings` secret\n   - The emptyDir is mounted at `/usr/share/elasticsearch/config/` in the main container (with subPath mounts for elasticsearch.yml, certs, and file-realm layering on top)\n\n6. **Snapshot repository registered** — `minio-repo` of type `s3` targeting the `es-backups` bucket using the `minio` client — all 3 nodes verified connectivity.\n\n7. **Snapshot created** — `snapshot-1` completed with `state: SUCCESS`, 3/3 shards successful, data confirmed written to MinIO."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1730,"cache_read_input_tokens":68922,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral